<h3>Local journeys on the District and Piccadilly lines</h3>

<ul>
	<li>For stations between Acton Town and Heathrow: Use the Central line via Ealing Broadway or the District line via Gunnersbury and follow purple signs for replacement&nbsp;bus A</li>
	<li>Replacement bus A runs every 7-10 minutes between Gunnersbury and Heathrow Central bus station calling at: Gunnersbury - Acton Town - Ealing Common - Ealing Broadway (for the Central line) - South Ealing - Northfields - Boston Manor - Osterley - Hounslow East* - Hounslow Central (stop at Bell Corner) - Hounslow West* - Hatton Cross - Heathrow Central bus station (for Terminals 2 &amp; 3)</li>
	<li>For Terminals 4 or 5, go to Terminals 2/3 and use free inter-terminal transfer services</li>
	<li>Bus A runs throughout the night and extends to Hammersmith and Heathrow Terminal 5 during Friday and Saturday Night Tube.</li>
	<li>For stations between Acton Town and Rayners Lane: Use the Central line via Hanger Lane, the District line via Gunnersbury or the Metropolitan line via Rayners Lane and follow blue signs for replacement&nbsp;bus E, which runs every 7-10 minutes</li>
	<li>replacement bus E calls at:&nbsp;<span style="line-height:115%"><span lang="EN"><span style="line-height:115%">Gunnersbury - Acton Town - Ealing Common - North Ealing - Hanger Lane (for the Central line and nearby Park Royal) - Alperton - Sudbury Town* - Sudbury Hill - South Harrow - Rayners Lane (for the Metropolitan line). </span></span></span></li>
	<li>
	<p>For stations between Rayners Lane and Uxbridge: use the Metropolitan line. For Chiswick Park: use local buses to or from Turnham Green or Gunnersbury</p>
	</li>
</ul>

<h4>Step-free journeys to or from Acton Town, Hounslow East, Hounslow West or Sudbury Town</h4>

<p>Gunnersbury station is not step-free. Speak to a member of staff before travelling.</p>

<p>Alternatively:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Acton Town &#45; use nearby Acton Central station for step-free access to London Overground services. Or use local bus 266 to Hammersmith for step-free access to the Circle, District, Hammersmith &amp; City or Piccadilly lines.</li>
	<li>Hounslow East &#45; use replacement bus A to Heathrow Central Bus station for step-free access to TfL Rail services. Or use local bus H37 to Richmond for step-free access to the District line and London Overground services.</li>
	<li>Hounslow West - use replacement bus A to Heathrow Central Bus station for step-free access to TfL Rail services. Or use local bus H91 to Hammersmith for step-free access to the Circle, District, Hammersmith &amp; City or Piccadilly lines.</li>
	<li>Sudbury Town &#45; use local bus H17 to Wembley Central for step-free access to the Bakerloo line and National Rail services. Or use local bus 92 to Greenford for step-free access to the Central line and National Rail services.<br />
	&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<h2>Travelling to or from Heathrow Airport</h2>

<p>Allow extra time for your journey, especially&nbsp;if you are flying out of Heathrow Airport.</p>

<h3>Taking luggage or buggies to the airport</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Take the District, Piccadilly, Circle or Hammersmith &amp; City lines to Hammersmith</li>
	<li>Non-stop coaches are running between Hammersmith&nbsp;and Heathrow Airport via the motorway&nbsp;every 3-8 minutes. There are porters and lifts at Hammersmith and Heathrow and extra space for luggage and buggies:
	<ul>
		<li>Between Terminal 5 and Hammersmith: follow green signs for coach B</li>
		<li>Between Terminal 2/3 and Hammersmith: follow orange signs for coach C</li>
		<li>During Night Tube, follow purple signs for all-stations bus A (which is wheelchair accessible)</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>For Terminal 4: go to Terminals 2/3 and use the free train or bus transfer services</li>
	<li>Coaches are not wheelchair-accessible</li>
</ul>
