<h3>Accessible routes to the airport</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Take the&nbsp;Hammersmith &amp; City line to Paddington</li>
	<li>TfL Rail runs every 30 minutes to and from Terminals 2, 3 &amp; 4.</li>
	<li>Speak to a member of staff for ramp access to TfL Rail trains</li>
	<li>For Terminal 5, go to Terminals 2/3 or 4 and use the free train or bus transfer services
	<ul>
		<li>Alternatively, use South Western Railway services between Waterloo and Feltham, for local bus 285 to Heathrow Central Bus station</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Only during Night Tube
	<ul>
		<li>Take the Piccadilly or District lines to Hammersmith</li>
		<li>Follow purple signs for extended all-stations replacement bus A to Terminals 2, 3 and 5 (which is wheelchair accessible)</li>
		<li>For Terminal 4, go to Terminals 2/3 or 5 and use the free train or bus transfer services</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

<h3>Paying for your travel</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Pay as you go with Oyster or contactless, or buy a paper Tube ticket</li>
	<li>Paper Tube tickets will be accepted on other services including TfL Rail betweeb Paddington and Heathrow and on South Western Railway trains between Waterloo and Feltham (via Hounslow)</li>
	<li>Paper Tube tickets will not be accepted on Heathrow Express trains between Paddington and Heathrow</li>
</ul>

<h2>Buses</h2>

<p>Sunday service running on Bank Holiday Monday&nbsp;27 May.</p>

<p>For the latest information on how buses are running, see our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/bus/status">bus status updates</a>.</p>

<p>Follow <a href="https://twitter.com/TfLBusAlerts">&#64;TfLBusAlerts</a> for news and service information.</p>

<h2>DLR</h2>

<p>We are running a Saturday service on Bank Holiday Monday (27 May)</p>

<p>See how the DLR is running on our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/">status updates</a> page.</p>

<p>Follow <a href="https://twitter.com/LondonDLR"> &#64;LondonDLR</a> for news and service information.</p>

<h2>London Overground</h2>

<h3 style="margin-bottom:10pt; margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-top:0cm">All weekend</h3>

<p>Gunnersbury station is likely to be very busy due to the Piccadilly and District line closures.</p>

<h3>Saturday&nbsp;25 May</h3>

<p>Euston to Watford Junction - Saturday service</p>

<h3>Sunday&nbsp;26 May</h3>

<p>No service between Clapham Junction and Willesden Junction. Use local buses via any reasonable route</p>

<p>&nbsp;Euston to&nbsp;Watford Junction -&nbsp;Sunday service</p>

<h3>Bank Holiday Monday 27 May</h3>

<ul>
	<li>An amended weekday service will run between&nbsp;Highbury &amp; Islington&nbsp;and New Cross, Clapham Junction, Crystal Palace and West Croydon</li>
	<li>An amended Saturday service will run:
	<ul>
		<li>between Gospel Oak&nbsp;and Barking</li>
		<li>between&nbsp;Euston and Watford Junction</li>
		<li>Between Liverpool Street and Enfield Town, Cheshunt (via Seven Sisters) and Chingford</li>
		<li>between Stratford&nbsp;and Richmond/Clapham Junction</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>A Saturday service will run between Romford&nbsp;and Upminster</li>
</ul>

<p>See how London Overground is running on our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/">status updates</a> page.</p>

<p>Follow <a href="http://twitter.com/LDNOverground">&#64;LDNOverground</a> on Twitter for news and service information.</p>

<h2>TfL Rail</h2>

<p>On Bank Holiday Monday&nbsp;27 May, we&nbsp;are running a Saturday service between Liverpool Street and Shenfield. Trains&nbsp;between Paddington and Heathrow are likely to be very busy because of the Piccadilly and District line closure.</p>

<p>See how&nbsp;TfL Rail&nbsp;is running on our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/">status updates</a> page.</p>

<p>Follow <a href="http://twitter.com/TfLRail">&#64;TfLRail</a> for news and service information.</p>

<h2>Trams</h2>

<p>On Sunday 26 May there is no service between Sandilands and Elmers End / Birkbeck until 09:00.</p>

<p>See how trams are running on our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/"> status updates</a> page.</p>

<p>Follow&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/TramsLondon">&#64;TramsLondon</a> for news and service information.</p>

<h2>Major roadworks</h2>

<p><a href="/status-updates/major-works-and-events/old-street-roundabout">Old Street Roundabout</a> will change to two-way traffic over the Bank Holiday&nbsp;weekend. City Road (south) and Old Street (west)&nbsp;will be temporarily closed over the weekend. Traffic and bus routes will be on diversion over the weekend. Access will be maintained on the Inner Ring Road.</p>

<p>If you are driving,&nbsp;walking or cycling in the area, take extra care especially when crossing the road.</p>

<h2>Driving</h2>

<p>There is no <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/driving/congestion-charge">Congestion Charge (CC)</a> on Monday&nbsp;27 May. The Congestion Charge resumes as normal on Tuesday&nbsp;28 May.</p>

<p>The <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/driving/ultra-low-emission-zone">Ultra Low Emission Zone (ULEZ)</a> remains in operation 24/7 throughout the bank holiday weekend.</p>

<p>For the latest information on London roads, see our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/traffic/status">traffic status updates map.</a></p>

<p>For news about traffic in London, follow <a href="https://twitter.com/TfLTrafficNews">&#64;TfLTrafficNews</a> on Twitter.</p>

<h2>Dial-a-Ride</h2>

<p>Services will run throughout the long weekend (for registered members only), but no regular bookings will operate on Bank Holiday Monday.</p>

<p>Please book in advance at the earliest opportunity.</p>

<p>For more details&nbsp; of services, see our <a href="/modes/dial-a-ride/index">Dial-a-Ride pages</a>.</p>

<h2>Emirates Air Line</h2>

<p>The cable car is running over the bank holiday weekend.</p>

<p>On Sunday, the cable car will open an hour later and run 09:00-23:00.</p>

<p>On Bank Holiday Monday&nbsp;27 May, services run from 09:00 until 22:00</p>

<p>See how the cable car is running in our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/cable-car/status">Status updates for Emirates&nbsp;Air Line.</a>&nbsp;Follow <a href="https://twitter.com/EmiratesAirLDN">&#64;EmiratesAirLine </a>on Twitter&nbsp;for news and service information.</p>

<h2>River</h2>

<h3>Bank Holiday Monday&nbsp;27 May</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Thames Clippers will run a weekend service</li>
	<li>Woolwich Ferry will run a one ferry service</li>
</ul>

<p>Follow<a href="https://twitter.com/tflriver">&nbsp;&#64;TfLRiver</a> for news and service information.</p>

<h2>Cycling</h2>

<p>Old Street Roundabout will change to two-way traffic over the Bank Holiday weekend. City Road (south) and Old Street (west) will be temporarily closed over the weekend. Traffic and bus routes will be on diversion over the weekend. Access will be maintained on the Inner Ring Road.</p>

<p>If you are cycling in the area, take extra care especially when crossing the road.</p>

<h2>Walking&nbsp;</h2>

<p>Old Street Roundabout will change to two-way traffic over the Bank Holiday weekend. City Road (south) and Old Street (west) will be temporarily closed over the weekend. Traffic and bus routes will be on diversion over the weekend. Access will be maintained on the Inner Ring Road.</p>

<p>If you are walking in the area, take extra care.</p>

<p>Closures are subject to change. For the latest information, see our six month look ahead for <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/cdn/static/cms/documents/track-closures.pdf">track </a>and <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/cdn/static/cms/documents/station-closures.pdf">stations</a>.</p>

<p>This page will be updated with more information as it becomes available.</p>
